Transcription.Text: The oval experiment at Wellingborough, though over-large, was clearly an attempt to reproduce on a large scale something of the openness of the meeting house. Worship. In its classic days there was enough of the Anabaptist and enough of the quaker in most congregationalists to ensure that any kind of fixed liturgy would be entirely unwelcome.
